---
import LogoStrip from '../../components/LogoStrip.astro'
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro'
---
<Section
  id="pedigree"
  label="Pedigree"
  headline="Built on the language ISDA picked for derivatives in 2018."
  variant="default"
>
  <p class="prose">
    Since 2018, ISDA and Digital Asset have jointly developed an open-source
    reference library in Daml, including a working IRS and CDS lifecycle
    implementation under the ISDA Common Domain Model
    (<a href="https://www.isda.org/2020/10/06/isda-and-digital-asset-launch-cdm-clearing-pilot-using-daml/" class="src" target="_blank" rel="noopener">source</a>).
    IRSForge sits one layer above that. It consumes Daml Finance, Digital Asset's
    derivatives library that encodes the same ISDA conventions, and wires the
    lifecycle, oracle, and settlement chain around the templates as shipped.
    Nothing reimplemented.
  </p>
  <LogoStrip />
  <blockquote class="quote">"We don't reimplement Daml Finance interfaces. We use them."</blockquote>
  <p class="if-link">
    <a href="https://docs.irsforge.com/architecture/daml-finance-interfaces">See the full interface map in the docs →</a>
  </p>
</Section>

<style>
  .prose { max-width: 60ch; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--color-fg-body); margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
  .src { color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-style: dotted; text-underline-offset: 3px; font-size: 0.875em; }
  .src:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .quote { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.5rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-accent); border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent); padding-left: 1.25rem; margin: 3rem auto; max-width: 50ch; }
  .if-link { text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; }
  .if-link a { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
